##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");
#make all percentages smaller than 1[$PERCENT]

$num = random(50,300,10);
$p1=random(2,9,1)/10;
$d1=$p1/100;
$ans1 = $d1*$num;

$ans2 = random(11,99,2)/100;
$b2 = random(310,500,10);
$a2 = $b2*$ans2/100;

$ans3 = random(1100,9900,100);
$p3 = random(2,9,1)/100;
$a3 = $p3/100*$ans3;

Context("LimitedNumeric");
$ans1 = Compute($ans1);
$ans2 = Compute($ans2);
$ans3 = Compute($ans3);

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Fill in the blanks:

a)    [_______]{$ans1} is [` [$p1]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

b)    [`[$a2]`] is [______]{$ans2} [`%`] of [` [$b2] `]?

c)    [`[$a3]`] is  [`[$p3]%`] of [______]{$ans3}?

END_PGML

##############################################

$s2 = $ans2/100;
$s3 = $p3/100;

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

This translation from English to math may help you remember the percentage formula.

    [` 2 \text{ is } 50% \text{ of } 4 \iff 2 = 0.5 \cdot 4 `]

a)   What is [` [$p1]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

    [``\begin{aligned} 
      x &= [$d1] \cdot [$num]\\
        &= [$ans1] 
      \end{aligned}``]

    So [` [$ans1] `] is [` [$p1]% `] of [` [$num] `].  
----
b)  [`[$a2]`] is what[`%`] of [` [$b2] `]? 

    [``
\begin{aligned}
  [$a2] &= \frac{x}{100} \cdot [$b2] \\
  100([$a2]) &= 100\cdot\frac{x}{100} \cdot [$b2] \\
  [$a200] &= x \cdot [$b2] \\
  \frac{[$a200]}{[$b2]} &= \frac{x \cdot [$b2]}{[$b2]} \\
  [$s2] &= x\\
  x &= [$s2]
\end{aligned}
    ``]

    So [` [$a2] `] is [` [$ans2]% `] of [` [$b2] `].  
----
c)  [`[$a3]`] is  [`[$p3]%`] of what? 

    [``
\begin{aligned}{2}
  [$a3] &= [$s3] \cdot x \\
  \frac{[$a3]}{[$s3]} &= \frac{[$s3] \cdot x}{[$s3]} \\
  [$ans3] &= x\\
  x &= [$ans3]
\end{aligned}
    ``]

    So [` [$a3] `] is [` [$p3]% `] of [` [$ans3] `].

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
